article.description: Kayla Tetschlag scored 25 points and Celeste Hoewisch added 14 to lead No. 17 Wisconsin-Green Bay to a 77-59 win over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Saturday.
article.headline: Green Bay handles Wis.-Milwaukee to clinch share of Horizon League title
article.linkText: Green Bay cruises to nab share of Horizon title
article.story:
MILWAUKEE --  Kayla Tetschlag scored 25 points and Celeste Hoewisch added 14 to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) to a 77-59 win over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Saturday.

The win clinched a share of the Horizon Conference title for the Phoenix (25-1, 14-0), who have won 16 straight games. They've won 23 straight conference games.

The Phoenix led most of the game, but could not put Milwaukee away. The Panthers cut the lead to 57-49 with 10:24 remaining when Sami Tucker scored on a driving layup and was fouled, and she made the free throw to complete the three-point play.

Green Bay went on an 11-2 run to grab a 68-51 lead with 5:36 remaining when Hannah Quilling hit two free throws. Milwaukee could get no closer than 12 the rest of the way.

Lindsay Laur led the Panthers (9-16, 6-8) with 17 points and eight rebounds, while Tucker added 14 points. But the team committed 23 turnovers that led to 30 points.
